channel.title: Playlist for gym
channel.description:
So i downloaded a time ago a playlist from youtube so i can listen to while at the gym from youtube:
[youtube]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_B789lus-JE[/youtube]
But after few weeks , it's not as good as it was before and i'm tired of hearing it all over and over.. So do you have any 1 - 2 Hours of electronic music or pump up music suggestions that you have heard?
I'd appreciate it!
lel,datenglishdoe.

item.title: Playlist for gym
item.dc:creator: @naseem142 naseem142
item.description:
@naseem142 wrote:

[quote=“Ruby, post:2, topic:547030”]I use all of these mixtapes/megamixes whenever I train. They never fail me. Especially Dan Healeys end of year 2013 mixtape. Phenomenal. Starts slow and gets you pumped and then adds in remixed versions of the biggest tunes of 2013 along with some golden oldies, bit outdated now but it’s still great. Click the link to see the full playlist, that’s just one megamix in the actual list.

https://www.youtube .com/watch?v=PAPw2kLa-i0&list=PLcbygBhMD2yTvTpQzmCJ9wV1sXniw8cv0&index=4

Not sure if you like bounce/minimal but it’s pretty fudgeing good for getting a buzz going if you ask me.[/quote]

Thanks mate, It is actually good. And i like most electronic music, or just some good pumping beat.
